<item>
            <title>[LU-14134] reduce credits for new writing potentially</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14134</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For new writting, Lustre reserve credits in worst cases, eg for 1M write, we need reserve more than 500 credits.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This means we need much more journal space than data for each write, which means we need large journal to reach good performance.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One of potential way to improve this could be we allow transaction restart for write commit&lt;br/&gt;
case.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
